This is my first backend project, developed as part of my journey to learn and implement core backend development concepts.

The project demonstrates the integration of various backend technologies and frameworks to build a dynamic and functional web application.

üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack

        Node.js

        Express.js

        MongoDB

        EJS (Embedded JavaScript Templates)

        Tailwind CSS


Key Features & Learnings

    API Development:

        Created RESTful and dynamic APIs to manage application data.

        Implemented structured routing and controllers for maintainability.

    Middleware & Modular Architecture:

        Gained a deep understanding of middleware functions and modular design.

        Enhanced project scalability by organizing logic into reusable modules.

   

    Authentication, Authorization & Security:

        Implemented JWT-based authentication for secure API access.

        Used cookies and sessions for user state management.

        Applied role-based access control for admin and user permissions.

        Secured passwords with bcrypt hashing before storing in the database.

        Handled login, logout, and protected routes efficiently.

    Database Operations (CRUD):

        Performed Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations using MongoDB.

        Established relationships between data models for efficient data handling.

    File Handling:

        Implemented file upload functionality using Multer.

        Managed file storage and validation efficiently.